    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-21T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-21T11:00:00-05:00" n="174"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d174">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/810.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to Great
                            Britain</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-21T16:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 21, 1912—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The British Government have instructed their Minister in Peking to cooperate with
                    his interested colleagues in protesting vigorously <pb facs="0233" n="117"
                        xml:id="pg_117"/> against the reported Belgian loan, discussed in your
                    telegraphic instruction of March 19, 7 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reid.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
